    <span class="h3 font-thin purple">How the competition works</span>
    <hr />
    <div class="clear">
        <p>
            Following our activation sessions, the brand values competition sets about looking for AIBers who can demonstrate how they live one or all of our new brand values already. 
        </p>

        <div class="row margin-bottom-10">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <ul>
                    <li class="purple">We put our customers first</li>
                    <li class="text-success">We are empowering</li>
                    <li class="text-primary">We are building trust and appreciation</li>
                    <li class="text-warning">We keep things simple</li>
                    <li class="text-info">We are better together</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 center">
                <img src="https://d3kx2j4tswsg1z.cloudfront.net/values/compass-large.png" alt="AIB Brand Values">
            </div>
        </div>


        <p>
            Which one of these values are you or your team great at living? Or perhaps your team embody all of these values? Well it’s time to share and inspire your colleagues with how you do it.
        </p>
        <hr/>
        <p>To enter the competition and be in with a chance of winning a prize, all you need to do is:</p>
        <ol>
            <li class="margin-bottom-10">Decide if you’d like to enter as an individual or as part of a team – for the purpose of this competition we’ve capped the size of a team being between 3 and 15 people. However you can enter numerous times as an individual and / or as a team.</li>
            <li class="margin-bottom-10">Select the value or value(s) you think you live well</li>
            <li class="margin-bottom-10">Come up with a creative way to demonstrate how you embody this value(s) – for example, this could be in the form of a film, a photo, a story, a poem or even a song! The more creative the better</li>
            <li class="margin-bottom-10">Come up with a name for your entry and submit it <a href="~/Home/Upload" class="text-info">here</a> on-line.</li>
        </ol>
        <hr/>
        <p>
            As entries come in they’ll be displayed on this site and your colleagues will be able to give you a thumbs up and write positive comments about why they like your entry so you can create fans as you go.
        </p>
        <p>
            The competition will be open for people to enter between <strong class="purple">27 August</strong> and <strong class="purple">8 October</strong>, that’s six weeks. Then on <strong class="purple">8 October</strong>, our judging panel will shortlist the entries down to ten – five individual entries and five team entries. The shortlisted entries will be posted on the site on <strong class="purple">14 October</strong> and we’ll all be able to vote on which individual and team entry should win. Votes will be counted and winners will be announced on <strong class="purple">27 October</strong>.
</p>
        <p>
            The good news is, you can access the site from anywhere - at work, on a mobile device or at home. Just remember your log in details and you can check in whenever suits you. You’ll have noticed above that you can enter by film - however until the Edge project delivers video functionality for us internally you won’t be able to upload or play the films in the office but you will of course be able to view them on a smart phone, iPad or a computer at home. 
        </p>
